    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for Model Risk Level 2. The CFD model demonstrates mean RHI prediction error of 8.3% against FDA experimental data, within the 15% acceptance threshold. Discretization error GCI of 3.2% satisfies the 5% requirement. Six factors are not assessed, consistent with MRL 2 requirements for a Class II device with medium model influence. The model is accepted as sufficiently credible to support worst-case hemolysis operating condition identification for the CPB COU.",
